  800-If you marshall your config to a String using a reflection based tool like Jackson, it will still be able to see the underlying value.
  801-In these cases, you would need to register a custom serializer.
  802:For the Jackson project, a `HopliteModule` object is available in the `hoplite-json` module.
  803-Register this with your Jackson mapper, like `mapper.registerModule(HopliteModule)` and then `Masked` values will be ouputted into Json as "****"
  804-
