  959-Hoplite embraces immutable config, but if you require that config is dynamic, then Hoplite provides a `ReloadableConfig` wrapper.
  960:This functionality is available by adding the module `hoplite-watch` to your build. The reloader requires a `ConfigLoader`
  961-and then accepts one or more `Watchable`s which cause the config to be reloaded when whatever they are watching is triggered.
  962-
  --
  995-| FixedIntervalWatchable | Triggers a reload at a fixed interval specified in millis.                                                               |
  996-| FileWatcher            | Triggers a reload whenever a file inside a given directory is modified.                                                  |
  997:| ConsulWatcher          | Triggers whenever a key is added, removed or updated in a `Consul` instance. Requires the `hoplite-watch-consul` module. |
