  614-| `arrow.core.Option<A>`                  | A `None` is used for null or undefined values, and present values are converted to a `Some<A>`.                                                                                                             |
  --
  617-| `arrow.core.Tuple4<A,B,C,D>`            | Converts an array of four elements into an instance of `Tuple4<A,B,C,D>`. Will fail if the array does not have exactly four elements.                                                                       |
  618-| `arrow.core.Tuple5<A,B,C,D,E>`          | Converts an array of five elements into an instance of `Tuple5<A,B,C,D,E>`. Will fail if the array does not have exactly five elements.                                                                     |
