ore processing.\n258-\n259:As of Hoplite 3, the `EnvironmentVariablesPropertySource` is applied by default and may be used to override other config properties\n260-directly. There is no longer any built-in support for the `config.override.` prefix. However, the optional `prefix` setting can still\n261-be used for the same purpose.\n--\n610-| `JMXPrincipal`                          | Creates an instance of `JMXPrincipal` for String values                                                                                                                                                     |\n611-| `Principal`                             | Creates an instance of `BasicPrincipal` for String values                                                                                                                                                   |\n612:| **Arrow**                               | Requires `hoplite-arrow` module                                                                                                                                                                             |\n613-| `arrow.data.NonEmptyList<A>`            | Converts arrays into a `NonEmptyList<A>` if the array is non empty. If the array is empty then an error is raised.                                                                                          |\n614-| `arrow.core.Option<A>`                  | A `None` is used for null or undefined values, and present values are converted to a `Some<A>`.                                                                                                             |\n--\n617-| `arrow.core.Tuple4<A,B,C,D>`            | Converts an array of four elements into an instance of `Tuple4<A,B,C,D>`. Will fail if the array does not have exactly four elements.                                                                       |\n618-| `arrow.core.Tuple5<A,B,C,D,E>`          | Converts an array of five elements into an instance of `Tuple5<A,B,C,D,E>`. Will fail if the array does not have exactly five elements.                                                                     |\n619:| **Hikari Connection Pool**              | Requires `hoplite-hikaricp` module                                                                                                                                                                          |\n620:| `HikariDataSource`                      | Converts nested config into a `HikariDataSource`. Any keys nested under the field name will be passed through to the `HikariConfig` object as the datasource is created. Requires `hoplite-hikaricp` module |\n621:| **Hadoop Types**                        | Requires `hoplite-hdfs` module                                                                                                                                                                              |\n622-| `org.apache.hadoop.fs.Path`             | Returns instances of HDFS Path objects                                                                                                                                                                      |\n623:| **CronUtils types**                     | Requires `hoplite-cronutils` module                                                                                                                                                                         |\n624-| `com.cronutils.model.Cron`              | Returns parsed instance of a cron expression                                                                                                                                                                |\n625:| **kotlinx datetime Types**              | Requires `hoplite-datetime` module                                                                                                                                                                          |\n626-| `kotlinx.datetime.LocalDateTime`        |                                                                                                                                                                                                             |\n627-| `kotlinx.datetime.LocalDate`            |                                                                                                                                                                                                             |\n628-| `kotlinx.datetime.Instant`              |                                                                                                                                                                                                             |\n629:| **AWS SDK types**                       | Requires `hoplite-aws` module                                                                                                                                                                               |\n630-| `com.amazonaws.regions.Region`          |                                                                                                                                                                                                             |\n631:| **Micrometer types**                    | Requires `hoplite-micrometer-xxx` modules                                                                                                                                                                   |\n632-| `io.micrometer.statsd.DatadogConfig`    | Converts a nested object to an instance of DatadogConfig                                                                                                                                                    |\n633-| `io.micrometer.statsd.PrometheusConfig` | Converts a nested object to an instance of PrometheusConfig                                                                                                                                                 |\n--\n661-\n662-\n663:## Preprocessors\n664-\n665-Hoplite supports what it calls preprocessors. These are just functions that are applied to every value as they are read from the underlying config file.\n--\n688-\n689-\n690:### Built-in Preprocessors\n691-\n692-These built-in preprocessors are registered automatically.\n--\n704-\n705-\n706:### Optional Preprocessors\n707-\n708:These preprocessors must be added to the `ConfigBuilder` before they take effect, and require extra modules to be added to the build.\n709-\n710-| Preprocessor                    | Function                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |\n711-|:--------------------------------|:-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n712:| `AwsSecretsManagerPreprocessor` | Replaces strings of the form awssm://key by looking up the value of 'key' from [AWS Secrets Manager](https://aws.amazon.com/secrets-manager/).<br/><br/>This preprocessor requires the `hoplite-aws` module to be added to the classpath.                                                                              |\n713:| `AzureKeyVaultPreprocessor`     | Replaces strings of the form azurekeyvault://key by looking up the value of 'key' from [Azure Key Vault](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/key-vault/).<br/><br/>This preprocessor requires the `hoplite-azure` module to be added to the classpath.                                                              |\n714:| `ParameterStorePreprocessor`    | Replaces strings of the form ${ssm:key} by looking up the value of 'key' from the [AWS Systems Manager Parameter Store](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/systems-manager/latest/userguide/systems-manager-parameter-store.html).<br/><br/>This preprocessor requires the `hoplite-aws` module to be added to the classpath. |\n715:| `ConsulConfigPreprocessor`      | Replaces strings of the form consul://key by looking up the value of 'key' from a [Consul](https://www.consul.io/) server.<br/><br/>This preprocessor requires the `hoplite-consul` module to be added to the classpath.                                                                                               |\n716:| `VaultSecretPreprocessor`       | Replaces strings of the form vault://key by looking up the value of 'key' from a [Vault](https://www.vaultproject.io/) instance.<br/><br/>This preprocessor requires the `hoplite-vault` module to be added to the classpath.                                                                                          |\n717:| `GcpSecretManagerPreprocessor`  | Replaces strings of the form `gcpsm://projects/{projectId}/secrets/{secretName}/versions/{version:latest}` by looking up the value from a [Google Cloud Secret Manager](https://cloud.google.com/secret-manager) instance.<br/><br/>This preprocessor requires the `hoplite-gcp` module to be added to the classpath.  |\n718-\n719-\n--\n800-If you marshall your config to a String using a reflection based tool like Jackson, it will still be able to see the underlying value.\n801-In these cases, you would need to register a custom serializer.\n802:For the Jackson project, a `HopliteModule` object is available in the `hoplite-json` module.\n803-Register this with your Jackson mapper, like `mapper.registerModule(HopliteModule)` and then `Masked` values will be ouputted into Json as \"****\"\n804-\n--\n958-\n959-Hoplite embraces immutable config, but if you require that config is dynamic, then Hoplite provides a `ReloadableConfig` wrapper.\n960:This functionality is available by adding the module `hoplite-watch` to your build. The reloader requires a `ConfigLoader`\n961-and then accepts one or more `Watchable`s which cause the config to be reloaded when whatever they are watching is triggered.\n962-\n--\n995-| FixedIntervalWatchable | Triggers a reload at a fixed interval specified in millis.                                                               |\n996-| FileWatcher            | Triggers a reload whenever a file inside a given directory is modified.                                                  |\n997:| ConsulWatcher          | Triggers whenever a key is added, removed or updated in a `Consul` instance. Requires the `hoplite-watch-consul` module. |\n998-\n999-\n--\n1003-## Add on Modules\n1004-\n1005:Hoplite makes available several other modules that add functionality outside of the main core module. They are in\n1006:seperate modules because they bring in dependencies from those projects and so the modules are optional.\n1007-\n1008-| Module                        | Function                                                                                                |\n1009-|:------------------------------|:--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n1010-| hoplite-arrow                 | Provides decoders for common arrow types                                                                |\n1011:| hoplite-aws                   | Provides decoders for aws `Region` type and a preprocessor for AWS Secrets Manager and Parameter Store. |\n1012:| hoplite-aws2                  | Provides decoders for aws `Region` type using the AWS v2 SDK.                                           |\n1013-| hoplite-azure                 | Provides a preprocessor for retreiving values from Azure Key Vault.                                     |\n1014-| hoplite-consul                | Provides a preprocessor for retreiving values from a Consul instance.                                   |\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1782554866197}}
