  1-# Changelog
  2-
  3:### 3.0.0
  4-
  5:* Breaking: the `EnvironmentVariablesPropertySource` now uses idiomatic environment variable format i.e. upper case (though lower
  6-case is still accepted), letters, and digits. **Single underscores** now separate path hierarchies.
  7:* Breaking: The `EnvironmentVariableOverridePropertySource` has been removed. The standard `EnvironmentVariablesPropertySource` is now
  8:loaded by default, and takes precedence over other default sources just like the `EnvironmentVariableOverridePropertySource`
  9-did. To maintain similar behavior, configure it with a filtering `prefix`.
  10-* Add the ability to load a series of environment variables into arrays/lists via the `_n` syntax.
  11-
  --
  42-
  43-### 2.6.5
  44-
  45:* Add `prefix` option to `EnvironmentVariablesPropertySource` which is then stripped from env vars before resolution is applied.
  46-
  47-### 2.6.4
  48-
  --
  59-
  60-### 2.6.1
  61-
  62:* Add fallback version of `Environment.forEnvVar`
  63:* Provide `Environment` to decoders and preprocessors through the `DecoderContext`.
  64-
  65-### 2.6.0
  66-
  67:* Added `Environment` abstraction
  68-* Added `XdgConfigPropertySource` for loading config from $XDG_CONFIG_HOME
  69-* Added support for [GCP Secrets Manager](https://cloud.google.com/secret-manager). To use import `hoplite-gcp` and set your keys to be `gcpsm://mykey`.
  70-* Added support for AWS Secrets Manager using Amazon's SDK version 2. The syntax is the same, but import `hoplite-aws2` instead of `hoplite-aws`.
  --
  95-
  96-### 2.5.0
  97-
  98:* Added an automatically registered `EnvironmentVariablesOverridePropertySource` which allows for environment variables of the form `config.override.foo` to be automatically resolved as `foo`.
  99-
  100-### 2.4.0
  101-
  --
  117-* Fixed anchors in yaml when using multiple files #307
  118-* Added `subscribe` to `ReloadableConfig`
  119-
  120:### 2.3.0
  121-
  122-* Added `Base64` type and decoder
  123-* Added `hoplite-micrometer-datadog` module
  --
  163-* Fixed unresolved error typo (#301)
  164-* Trim input keys in `AwsSecretsManagerPreprocessor`
  165-* Better errors when key are missing in `AwsSecretsManagerPreprocessor`
  166:* Updated default obfuscator to not obfuscate non-strings (#299)
  167-* AWS ParameterStorePathPropertySource should support GetParametersByPathResult's nextToken (#295)
  168-
  169-### 2.0.3
  170-
  171:* Added `allowEmptyTree` on `ConfigLoaderBuilder` to _not_ error if all property sources return no values.
  172-
  173-### 2.0.2
  174-
  --
  178-### 2.0.1
  179-
  180-* Improved error messages from AWS Secrets Manager
  181:* Adjusted default obfuscator to obfuscate all fields
  182-* Fixed arg names used in constructor error message
  183-
  184-### 2.0.0
  --
  188-* Requires Kotlin 1.6 or higher
  189-* Requires JDK 11 or higher
  190-* `ConfigLoader.Builder` has been removed and replaced with `ConfigLoaderBuilder` which has clearer semantics around
  191:  defaults, and how to override defaults.
  192:* The env vars property source is no longer registered by default. Env vars are typically used to override specific
  193-  config values, not as an entire source of values, so this avoids some subtle runtime bugs.
  194-* Using an unresolved substitution value, eg ${foo} where foo doesn't exist, is now an error.
  195-* The `ConfigLoader.loadConfig` functions that accept a File or Path have been removed to simply the config loader
  --
  201-
  202-#### New Features
  203-
  204:* `ConfigLoaderBuilder.report` has been added to output a report of the property sources, the resolved config values (
  205-  obfuscated), and which config values were unused.
  206:* `ConfigLoaderBuilder.strict` mode reports unused config values at any level. If a property source provides a value
  207-  that is not used, the config loader will error when strict mode is on.
  208-* Multiple `@ConfigAlias` annotations are now supported per field
  209-* Better error handling on preprocessors.
  --
  232-
  233-### 1.4.11
  234-
  235:* Added order to defaults (Sources, Preprocessors and ParamMappers) (#229) - David Gomes
  236-
  237-### 1.4.10
  238-
  --
  246-### 1.4.8
  247-
  248-* Added support for watchers via the `hoplite-watc
