at is not used, the config loader will error when strict mode is on.\n208-* Multiple `@ConfigAlias` annotations are now supported per field\n209-* Better error handling on preprocessors.\n--\n232-\n233-### 1.4.11\n234-\n235:* Added order to defaults (Sources, Preprocessors and ParamMappers) (#229) - David Gomes\n236-\n237-### 1.4.10\n238-\n--\n246-### 1.4.8\n247-\n248-* Added support for watchers via the `hoplite-watch` and `hoplite-watch-consul` modules.\n249:* Added config builder option to not include the default decoders and processors.\n250-\n251-### 1.4.7\n252-\n--\n263-\n264-### 1.4.4\n265-\n266:* Adds basic command line property source. (#217)\n267-\n268-### 1.4.3\n269-\n--\n285-  who have written their own custom PropertySource.\n286-* Added `@ConfigAlias` to allow a data class field to map to multiple values. #197\n287-* Added strict option to `ConfigLoader.Builder` to throw an error if a config value is unused. Lenient mode is still the\n288:  default. #187\n289-* Bumped all module deps to latest versions\n290-\n291-### 1.3.15\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1782554922438}}
